… the dissolution of the Lao People’s Revolutionary Party. That is the most important event because it has given Laos a new beginning. With the Soviet Union no longer helping develop our country, we had to take new steps. At the Third Plenum in Vientiane on October 26–27, 1991, five decisions were made that completely changed the Party’s political moderation, ideology, and political economic system. Those five decisions formed what is known as Policy 141. We must thank our predecessors for doing those five things:
) the resolution of the Police Policy that took military action against some provinces; ) the economic reform policy; ) the ideology reform policy to replace Maoism by Leninism, thus closing a 25year long phase of democratic centralisation; ) the policy change to fully construct socialism according to our own model; ) the decision to widen socialist theory with, in particular, the knowledge and culture of socialism as seen in the West, including liberal democracy and private capitalism.
